This paper deals with the problem of rendezvous in Cognitive Radio Networks, which is a subfield of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The paper also involves optimization techniques for achieving fast rendezvous, which falls under Information Theory (cs.IT) and Systems and Control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of dynamic environments on the rendezvous problem, which is related to Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) and Cognitive Radio (cs.CR).
